  "title": "HR Executive",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Full Spectrum HR Work duties and administrative support role and advisor to manager in charge</li><li>Work with line managers on manpower requirements, employee relations issues, compensation and benefits matter, HR initiatives, and other HR matters;</li><li>Administration of workmen compensation, MOM reporting, insurance claim, etc;</li><li>Ensure that HR policies and practices are in compliance with prevailing statutory regulations;</li><li>Identify training and development needs of employees and propose training programs;</li><li>Work pass applications, renewals and cancellation;</li><li>Ensure timely update of employees’ database, proper filing system and smooth office administration;</li><li>Process payroll on a timely basis such as computation of monthly salaries and deductions;</li><li>Other ad-hoc duties as assigned</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree holder in Human Resources Management or HR related is preferred;</li><li>Preferably 3 years in relevant HR administration role; HR policy planning; HR full spectrum</li><li>Well versed with Singapore Employment Act and labor legislation;</li><li>Strong interpersonal skills to work with key decision makers and various levels of employees;</li><li>Working experience with InfoTech or any HRMS systems;</li><li>Organized and able to take stress</li><li>Prior Construction Background will be preferred</li></ul><p>Suitable candidates are encouraged to apply this position via Apply Now button or email to <strong>Career@kah.com.sg</strong></p><p><em>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</em></p>",
